？？？: I hope those diplomats aren't too hard on mom...
？？？: So stupid that I left my veil at home. But there should still be one stashed in the hall somewhere... Let's see if it's still there.
？？？: Agh, ouch! Why are there people out here?

Jia-Shen: I am not a turtle! I'm a tortoise, darnit! 
...Wait, don't change the subject!
Jia-Shen: These herbs... Ah! So yer here to steal our medicine!
？？？: No! No, that's not it...!
Jia-Shen: Save it for the guards!
Alliance Warrior: Who's there!?
？？？: (Crap! It's the Alliance guards!)
Alliance Warrior: Master Jia-Shen, are you alright?
Jia-Shen: I'm fine, but just now...
Jia-Shen: ...So that's what happened.
Alliance Warrior: A human... could they be a diplomat from the Kingdom of the Sun?
Jia-Shen: I don't reckon so, she wasn't dressed like one...
Alliance Warrior: We've got sentries everywhere. If she's not a diplomat, how could she have gotten in?
Jia-Shen: Well, the way she handled herself wasn't much like those Sun folk either...
Alliance Warrior: Hmph... you must be mistaken, Master Jia-Shen. You'll see once we catch her.
Jia-Shen: Now hold on...!
Jia-Shen: ...Seems like they really don't like us diplomats.
Jia-Shen: Now what? Weren't you headed out to round 'em up?
Alliance Warrior: I almost forgot—the arbiter will see you now. The ambassador from the Kingdom of the Sun wants you there as soon as possible.
Jia-Shen: Alright, I'll head over. Thank you kindly.
Jia-Shen: (Well I guess I've got more important things to worry about than some thief... for now.)
Jia-Shen: Desert Kingdom Ambassador Jia-Shen at your service, arbiter ma'am.
Maeok: I heard you started as an exchange student from the Turtle Tribe. Amazing that you've come so far as to be appointed ambassador.
Jia-Shen: Naw, it's nothin'. I guess I'm just well-versed in the cultures of both kingdoms is all.
Maeok: Is that so...
Maeok: And Ace Aldric, you are the ambassador to the Kingdom of the Sun?
Maeok: The twelve nobles... you do have an exquisite air about you, indeed.
Ace: Thank you for your kind words, Arbiter Maeok.
Ace: Yet what we will be discussing today is of great importance to our kingdoms. Please forgive me if appear out of line.
Maeok: Yes, I have read your letters, but... Were the two queens truly attacked?
Ace: Does the arbiter believe we would joke about such a thing?
Maeok: Ah, of course not...! Otherwise, I would have never delayed our Martial Arts Tournament sign-ups just to address the situation.
Maeok: What you have described is, well... monumental. I must look into it with the utmost seriousness.
Ace: We are truly grateful for your aid, and do not wish to take up more of the Alliance's precious time.
Ace: So I will cut to the chase.
Maeok: This gunpower... why does it look like an Udumbara flower?
Maeok: And this—a Martial Arts Tournament invitation!?
Ace: Whoever attacked Queen Angelia used these to disguise the bomb.
Ace: Thankfully, she got out of the way in time. She wasn't harmed, but...
Jia-Shen: Queen Diana got the same thing. Her injuries aren't severe, but she was hurt...
Ace: We haven't released this information publicly. On the record, this is just a regular diplomatic visit.
Maeok: This... someone is being framed, that much is clear.
Ace: Of course. But the problem is—
Ace: —In both kingdoms, these letters were delivered through official diplomatic channels.
Maeok: You mean, the attacker might not be a civilian? They could be internal?
Ace: We're not sure. But it is clear that not just any commoner can use those channels.
Ace: Both our kingdoms have already run a detailed check on everyone involved in the delivery of these letters. There's nothing out of the ordinary.
Maeok: ...Are you implying that our culprit is from the East Alliance?
Ace: No, but we hope that for the sake of our kingdoms' good standings, you would assign some of your people to help investigate.
Maeok: Impossible! Our tournament is right around the corner! There's no one I could spare!
Ace: Then we ask you, arbiter, to put your tournament on hold, temporarily, until this is sorted out.
Maeok: That's out of the question!
Ace: From our perspective, this is a wholly rational request. Or, does the Alliance wish to be seen as harboring terrorists?
Maeok: Ambassador Aldric, with all due respect, I ask you to watch your tone.
Jia-Shen: Yer mistaken, Arbiter Maeok, ma'am. What Ace here means is that, this would help the East Alliance clear their name, too.
Maeok: We do not need outside assistance to "clear our name".
Ace: Your fortitude is admirable, Arbiter Maeok, but—
Ace: If one day you were to be the target of our kingdom's unrest, I can't help but wonder if that fortitude wouldn't waver.
Maeok: Are you... are you threatening me!?
Ace: Threaten is too harsh a word, arbiter. I am simply presenting you with options.
Maeok: ...Jia-Shen, is this how you feel?
Jia-Shen: ...The Desert Kingdom stands with the Kingdom of the Sun.
Maeok: Please... let me think this over...
